   - `= g (f (f.symm (g.symm t)))`
   - `= g ((f ∘ f.symm) (g.symm t))`
   - Since `f ∘ f.symm = id_R` (because `f` is an equivalence), this becomes `g (id_R (g.symm t))`
   - `= g (g.symm t)`
   - Since `g` is an equivalence, `g ∘ g.symm = id_T`.

